  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Beyond the perturbation theory the tadpole term violates explicitly the transversality condition of the full gluon self-energy. However, we have formulated a general method which makes it possible for the ghosts to cancel the longitudinal component of the full gluon propagator even if the tapole term is explicitly present. At the same time, the Slavnov-Taylor identity for the full gluon propagator is always preserved. All other Slavnov-Taylor identities are not affected and the color currents are conserved as well. The tadpole contribution is not surviving in the perturbation theory regime when the gluon momentum goes to infinity.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
